headline: J.M. Smucker plans to remove artificial colors from its jams and other products by the end of 2027
summary: J.M. Smucker Co. plans to remove artificial colors from its products by the end of 2027. Orrville, Ohio-based Smucker said Thursday it will also remove synthetic dyes from foods sold to K-12 schools...

headline: JM Smucker moves on colour additives
summary: The changes will affect its sugar-free fruit spreads, ice cream toppings and products within its Hostess brand portfolio.

headline: JM Smucker latest food maker to commit to removing artificial dyes
summary: The Uncrustables and Twinkie maker plans to remove synthetic colors from its consumer food products by the end of 2027.
